                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00R296/4110b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Edge</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-24T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 24, 1931—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>273. I would like to know when France will expect to get back from the Bank for
                    International Settlements the funds which the Bank would advance under the
                    French proposal to other European countries out of the unconditional payments
                    made by Germany to France and transmitted by France to the Bank. This is in
                    confirmation of the inquiry which I made on the telephone this morning. Please
                    cable me urgently when you have acquired this information.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
